### Replication and Migration Setup with Memory Synced RxStorage

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-storage-memory-synced.html

This example illustrates setting up replication and migration using a parent database. It first creates a parent RxDatabase with IndexedDB storage, performs replication on it, and then creates an equal memory-synced RxDatabase for application use, ensuring the parent database is created first for migration purposes.

```typescript
const parentStorage = getRxStorageIndexedDB();
const memorySyncedStorage = getMemorySyncedRxStorage({
    storage: parentStorage,
    keepIndexesOnParent: true
});
const databaseName = 'mydata';
/** * Create a parent database with the same name+collections * and use it for replication and migration. * The parent database must be created BEFORE the memory-synced database * to ensure migration has already been run. */
const parentDatabase = await createRxDatabase({
    name: databaseName,
    storage: parentStorage
});
await parentDatabase.addCollections({ /* ... */ });
replicateRxCollection({
    collection: parentDatabase.myCollection,
    /* ... */
});
/** * Create an equal memory-synced database with the same name+collections * and use it for writes and queries. */
const memoryDatabase = await createRxDatabase({
    name: databaseName,
    storage: memorySyncedStorage
});
await memoryDatabase.addCollections({ /* ... */ });
```

