### Example Document Structure for RxDB Sync

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication.md

This TypeScript example illustrates the expected structure of a document for RxDB replication. It includes an `id` for primary identification, a `name` and `lastName` for data, `updatedAt` for deterministic sorting by write time, and `_deleted` to indicate deletion status, crucial for replication.

```typescript
const docData = {
    "id": "foobar",
    "name": "Alice",
    "lastName": "Wilson",
    /**
     * Contains the last write timestamp
     * so all documents writes can be sorted by that value
     * when they are fetched from the remote instance.
     */
