### Implement RxDB Pull Handler on Client

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication-http.md

This client-side code configures the pull handler for RxDB replication. It fetches documents from a specified server URL based on the last checkpoint, returning the documents and the new checkpoint for subsequent syncs. Dependencies include the `fetch` API.

```typescript
// > client.ts
const replicationState = await replicateRxCollection({
    /* ... */
    pull: {
        async handler(checkpointOrNull, batchSize){
            const updatedAt = checkpointOrNull ? checkpointOrNull.updatedAt : 0;
            const id = checkpointOrNull ? checkpointOrNull.id : '';
            const response = await fetch(
                `https://localhost/pull?updatedAt=${updatedAt}&id=${id}&limit=${batchSize}`
            );
            const data = await response.json();
            return {
                documents: data.documents,
                checkpoint: data.checkpoint
            };
        }

    }
    /* ... */
});
```

