### WebSocket Connection for Real-time Replication Stream

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication.md

Sets up a WebSocket connection to receive real-time data updates for RxDB replication. The `pullStream$` Subject emits incoming data, which includes document batches and checkpoints. The connection automatically handles reconnections and emits a 'RESYNC' signal upon re-establishing connection after an outage to ensure data consistency.

```javascript
const pullStream$ = new Subject();
let firstOpen = true;
function connectSocket() {
    const socket = new WebSocket('wss://example.com/api/sync/stream');
    socket.onmessage = event => pullStream$.next(event.data);
    socket.onclose = () => connectSocket();
    socket.onerror = () => socket.close();
    socket.onopen = () => {
        if(firstOpen) {
            firstOpen = false;
        } else {
            pullStream$.next('RESYNC');
        }
    }
}
```

